dmenu - dynamic menu
====================
dmenu is an efficient dynamic menu for X.


Requirements
------------
In order to build dmenu you need the Xlib header files.


Installation
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup (dmenu is installed into
the /usr/local namespace by default).

Afterwards enter the following command to build and install dmenu
(if necessary as root):

    make clean install


Patches
-------
- Center patch <https://tools.suckless.org/dmenu/patches/center/>
- Grid patch <https://tools.suckless.org/dmenu/patches/grid/>
- Gridnav patch <https://tools.suckless.org/dmenu/patches/gridnav/>
- Border patch <https://tools.suckless.org/dmenu/patches/border/>
    - With custom border selection.
- Numbers patch <https://tools.suckless.org/dmenu/patches/numbers/>
- Fuzzy match patch <https://tools.suckless.org/dmenu/patches/fuzzymatch/>
- Fuzzy highlight patch <https://tools.suckless.org/dmenu/patches/fuzzyhighlight/>
- Colored Caret patch <https://tools.suckless.org/dmenu/patches/colored-caret/>

Running dmenu
-------------
See the man page for details.
